Human rights will no longer be part of the Conservative Party's trade talks, Anne-Marie Trevelyan said in a letter to MPs, arguing she believed "free trade agreements are not generally the most effective or targeted tool to advance human rights issues". The drastic shift in the Tories' approach comes as the UK is attempting to sign a deal with Gulf countries including Saudi Arabia, Bahrain and the United Arab Emirates â€“ all well-known for their poor human rights records. The bombshell change comes after Ms Trevelyan told the House of Commons last October that trade "will not come at the expense of human rights" and that talks on free trade agreements would create an "opportunity to open discussions" on such issues. The revelation has sparked anger among human rights campaigners. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...